{"lemma":"آبِقٌ","slug":"آبِقٌ","root":"#.ب.ق","root_slug":"_-ب-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ب-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"آبِقٌ","root":"أبق","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n58",""],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A2%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%82%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n58","headword_ar":"اَبَقَ","root":"Abq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.,) which is the most common form, (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TS, Mgh, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) so in the copies of the K in the place of"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abiqa","text_ar":"اَبِقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IDrd, Msb, K;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibaAqN","text_ar":"اـِبَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboqN","text_ar":"اَبْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaqN","text_ar":"اَبَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or the first of these is a simple subst., and the second and third are the inf. ns.; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a slave)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from his master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being induced to do so by"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear, or severity of work:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:) thus the signification is restricted in the 'Eyn: (Msb:) and in this case, the law ordains that the slave shall be restored; but if the act arise from severity of work or from fear, he is not to be restored: (Lth, TA:) in the Kur xxxvii. 140, it is said of Jonas, (T, Bd,) because he fled from his people without the permission of his Lord: (Bd:) and it is also, tropically, said of a fish: (Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a slave)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hid himself, and then went away:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA^b~q","text_ar":"تابّق","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or this signifies, simply,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he hid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"concealed, himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he confined, restricted, limited, restrained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"withheld, himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or it has both of the last two significations: (Sgh:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he abstained"},{"kind":"text","text":"from a thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as from a sin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crime."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K *.) A poet says, (S,) namely, 'Ámir Ibn—Kaab, (AZ,) or 'Ámán Ibn-Kaab, or, as some say, Ghámán, (AA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"↓ \n      A^alaA qaAlato bahaAni wa lamo taA^ab~aqo\n                      \n                     \n                        kabirota walaA yaliyqu bika Aln~aEiymu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Now surely Baháni said, and she did not hide herself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did not restrain herself, Thou hast grown old, and enjoyment doth not befit thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she did not hide herself"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her mind], but said openly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she did not go far"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from the person whom she addressed, or from the truth]; so says AZ, taking it from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibaAqN","text_ar":"اـِبَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as relating to a slave: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she did not abstain"},{"kind":"text","text":"from her speech, as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from a sin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crime:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she did not disdain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scorn."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) AHát says that he asked As respecting ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA^b~q","text_ar":"تابّق"},{"kind":"text","text":", and he answered that he knew it not. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","TS","Mgh","K","T","Lth","TA","Bd","M","Sgh","AZ","AA","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A2%D8%A8%D9%82/","headword_ar":"آبق","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=22749#cf0c3d","body_html":"<span>الآبق: هو المملوك الذي يفر من مالكه قصدًا. </span>"}]}}